[
  "Son of a rubber trader, Prajogo Pangestu got his start in the timber business in the late 1970s.",
  "His company PT Barito Pacific Timber went public in 1993 and changed its name to Barito Pacific after cutting back on its timber business in 2007.",
  "In 2007 Barito Pacific acquired 70% of petrochemical firm Chandra Asri, which also trades on the Indonesia Stock Exchange.",
  "In 2011 Chandra Asri merged with Tri Polyta Indonesia and became the country's largest integrated petrochemical producer.",
  "Chandra Asri Petrochemical teamed with French tire manufacturer Michelin in 2015 to develop a synthetic rubber plant in Indonesia."
]